## 4. **Microsoft.Agents.AI (v1.0.0)**
Concrete implementations for agent building.

### ChatClientAgent - Agent Wrapping IChatClient

```csharp
public class ChatClientAgent : AIAgent
{
    // Delegates to an IChatClient
    public IChatClient ChatClient { get; }
    public ChatOptions ChatOptions { get; set; }
    public AIContextProvider[] AIContextProviders { get; set; }
    public ChatHistoryProvider? ChatHistoryProvider { get; set; }
    public string Instructions { get; set; }
}

public class ChatClientAgentOptions
{
    public string Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public string Description { get; set; }
    public string Instructions { get; set; }
    public ChatOptions ChatOptions { get; set; }
    public AIContextProvider[] AIContextProviders { get; set; }
    public ChatHistoryProvider? ChatHistoryProvider { get; set; }
    // ... more configuration
}

public class ChatClientAgentRunOptions : AgentRunOptions
{
    public Func<IChatClient>? ChatClientFactory { get; set; }
    public ChatOptions? ChatOptions { get; set; }
}
```

### Agent Builder - Pipeline Pattern for Agents

```csharp
public class AIAgentBuilder
{
    public AIAgentBuilder(AIAgent innerAgent);
    public AIAgentBuilder(Func<IServiceProvider, AIAgent> innerAgentFactory);

    // Add middleware
    public AIAgentBuilder Use(Func<AIAgent, AIAgent> agentFactory);
    public AIAgentBuilder Use(Func<AIAgent, IServiceProvider, AIAgent> agentFactory);
    public AIAgentBuilder Use(
        Func<IEnumerable<ChatMessage>, AgentSession, AgentRunOptions, 
            Func<...>, CancellationToken, Task> middleware);

    // Add context providers
    public AIAgentBuilder UseAIContextProviders(params MessageAIContextProvider[] providers);

    public AIAgent Build(IServiceProvider? services = null);
}

// Convenience extension
public static AIAgentBuilder AsBuilder(this AIAgent agent);
```

### Agent Middleware

```csharp
// Automatic function invocation for agents
public class FunctionInvocationDelegatingAgent : AIAgent
{
    // Automatically invokes functions called by the LLM
}

// Logging
public class LoggingAgent : AIAgent { }

// OpenTelemetry
public class OpenTelemetryAgent : AIAgent { }

// Chat history persistence
public class ChatHistoryMemoryProvider : ChatHistoryProvider
{
    // Manages conversation memory
}

// Message compaction (summarization, truncation, etc.)
public class CompactionProvider
{
    // Compacts messages in history to fit token limits
}
```

### Skills System

```csharp
// Define skills/tools from files or code
public class AgentSkillsProvider
{
    public IAsyncEnumerable<AgentSkill> GetSkillsAsync();
}

public class AgentSkill
{
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public string Description { get; set; }
    public AIFunction? Function { get; set; }
    public IDictionary<string, object> Metadata { get; set; }
}

// File-based skills
public class AgentFileSkillsSource : AgentSkillsSource
{
    // Load skills from .yaml files
}

// In-memory skills
public class AgentInMemorySkillsSource : AgentSkillsSource { }
```

---

## Key Patterns & Usage

### 1. **Building a Simple Chat Pipeline**
```csharp
var innerClient = new YourChatClient(apiKey);
var pipeline = new ChatClientBuilder(innerClient)
    .UseFunctionInvocation()
    .UseLogging()
    .UseOpenTelemetry(loggerFactory)
    .Build();

var response = await pipeline.GetResponseAsync(messages, options);
```

### 2. **Creating Functions for Tool Calling**
```csharp
// From a method
public class Tools
{
    [Function("Gets the weather")]
    public string GetWeather(
        [Description("City name")] string city,
        [Description("Celsius or Fahrenheit")] string unit = "C")
    {
        return $"Weather in {city} is sunny";
    }
}

var tools = new []
{
    AIFunctionFactory.Create(
        typeof(Tools).GetMethod("GetWeather")!,
        new Tools(),
        new AIFunctionFactoryOptions 
        { 
            Name = "get_weather",
            Description = "Gets current weather"
        })
};

// Use in options
var options = new ChatOptions { Tools = tools.Cast<AITool>().ToList() };
```

### 3. **Building a Multi-Agent System**
```csharp
var agent1 = new ChatClientAgent(chatClient1) { Name = "Agent1" };
var agent2 = new ChatClientAgent(chatClient2) { Name = "Agent2" };

var pipeline = new AIAgentBuilder(agent1)
    .Use((innerAgent, services) => new LoggingAgent(innerAgent))
    .Use((innerAgent, services) => new FunctionInvocationDelegatingAgent(innerAgent))
    .Build();

var response = await pipeline.RunAsync("What's the weather?");
```

### 4. **Function Invocation with Approval**
```csharp
var approvalRequired = new ApprovalRequiredAIFunction(deleteFunction);

var options = new ChatOptions 
{ 
    Tools = new AITool[] { approvalRequired } 
};

// When FunctionInvokingChatClient encounters this:
// 1. It emits ToolApprovalRequestContent instead of invoking
// 2. Awaits ToolApprovalResponseContent from the caller
// 3. Then invokes if approved, or rejects if denied
```

---

## Summary

| Feature | Package | Key Type |
|---------|---------|----------|
| **Chat Interface** | Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions | `IChatClient` |
| **Messages** | Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions | `ChatMessage`, `ChatOptions`, `ChatResponse` |
| **Tool Calling** | Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions | `AITool`, `AIFunction`, `FunctionCallContent` |
| **Function Factory** | Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions | `AIFunctionFactory` |
| **Pipelines** | Microsoft.Extensions.AI | `ChatClientBuilder` |
| **Function Invocation** | Microsoft.Extensions.AI | `FunctionInvokingChatClient` |
| **Agents** | Microsoft.Agents.AI.Abstractions | `AIAgent`, `AgentSession` |
| **Chat Agent** | Microsoft.Agents.AI | `ChatClientAgent`, `AIAgentBuilder` |
| **Skills** | Microsoft.Agents.AI | `AgentSkillsProvider`, `AgentSkill` |

All these APIs support streaming, cancellation tokens, and seamless integration with dependency injection in .NET 10.

